 No, I'm not referring to in-game marriages.<br><br>What would you consider the ideal marriage in regards to how it related to EQ?<br><br>Would it be your spouse leaving you to play whenever you want? Would it be a spouse that plays as well, but still gives you freedom in game to hang out with friends? How about a spouse that plays and hangs out with you in game?<br><br>Some folks have said that a perfect EQ marriage was "sex, eq, and food."<br><br>If you are married, give us your stories (good or bad) as they relate to EQ. Also, if you are single, what would you be looking for in a wife if you are not ready to give up EQ?<br> <p><img src=http://www.garlic.com/~hypatia/images/staff.gif width=460 height=40><br><i>Everybody loves a rose. Will you be thankful for the thorns?</i><br><a href="http://www.kaizenx.com/quickcharinfo.asp?charname=Martigan" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.kaizenx.com/images/nbnwkx1.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 584<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 7:30:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> Every relationship is different.<br><br>For me, I wouldn't play EQ more than 5-6 hours a week if my wife didn't play with me...same guild...usually same group.<br><br><br><br> <p><CENTER>GMF Virtuoso</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uglorianafrostglitter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloriana Frostglitter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1561<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 8:11:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> EQ and SOs</span><hr size=1> John gave me EQ for a birthday gift in 1999.  I had a lot of trouble getting started with the game so he started a character to get the hang of the game in order to give me some pointers.<br><br>At the time, we had one account and one computer.  Realizing that we were both really enjoying the game, we bought a second account.  John kept his enchanter and I started a new shaman on the second account.<br><br>In March of 2000, we bought a second computer and started grouping together.  We had a really good time and fell in with a regular group of friends and played nearly every night.  I can't imagine playing EQ with John and NOT grouping together (exp not raiding).  We joined the same guild.<br><br>Late last summer, John managed to kick the EQ habit and retired his 57 enchanter, Ving.  We're both very computer oriented people and our computers are still side by side, so we still spend a lot of time together doing different things on the computer.  <br><br>The good thing is, he understands the game and the addiction.  I don't think I could play EQ as much as I do if my significant other didn't &quot;get&quot; EQ: the lack of a pause button, the fact that others are depending on you in game, the lingo, the stories. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kidin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 9:07:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ and a happy marriage</span><hr size=1> Hail,<br><br>It took me a LONG time to convince my spouse to play.<br>Watched over my shoulder, but couldn't really &quot;get&quot; the game for some time.<br><br>Finally the hook sank in, and we play regularly together (and separately) almost every day now.  Getting the second account took much longer for us, but it did happen. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We paid for a character transfer rather than one of us start again.  We're both rather attached to our primary characters.<br><br>(Rather funny, Glori, we're an Ench/Shaman combo as well!)<br><br>Before we both played, Everquest was a slight strain on our marriage.  Missed family dinners, late night CR's causing lack of sleep and thus a shorter fuse on my temper and increased irritability the following day, etc.<br><br>Since we both play now, it adds to the time we spend together, which I think is a good thing, although the game still interferes sometimes with our other plans if we let it.<br><br>The game is what you make of it.<br>A marriage is also, although magnified by a large factor. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Take care, <p><select name=Frekkels><option>Frekkels of E. Marr<option>Clan Battle Axe Member<option>Barbarian Shaman  (54)<option>Master Potter (204)<option>Master Smith (200)<option>Master Fletcher (192)<option>Master Brewer  (174)<option>Master Fisher (172)<option>Master Cook (161)<option>Master Tailor  (158)<option>Master Alchemist (102)<option>Master Drunk (200)<option>Master Swimmer (200)</select></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaishen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aishen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1111<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 9:14:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> I couldn't deal with playing EQ simultaneously with my husband but not playing with him (same group, same guild, etc.)<br><br>When we first started playing he was higher level and we never grouped, so we just sort of zoned off into our own separate worlds whenever we played.  That was pure torture for the both of us, so he started a new character and we were both late 30's/early 40's when we started playing together.  Ever since then we've been a packaged deal and have chugged to 58 together.<br><br>What's great is when I need to afk, he can take over for me and when he needs to afk, I can take over for him since our computers are next to each other.  I think it's a great setup because we're both still doing what we enjoy and we get to do it together interactively.  The day he quits, I quit, because I don't want to just sit at the computer all by my lonesome without my best friend at my side. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uchiteng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiteng</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1648<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 9:26:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> My wife and I both play MMORGS but:<br><br>We NEVER group together. It always ends in a fight if we try.<br><br>Thing is, she takes far more @#%$ from her groupmates than she would ever<br>take from me, either at home, or in game.<br><br>We do belong to the same guild, and we get along just fine. We just dont group.<br> <p>“It is clear that the individual who persecutes a man, his brother, because he is not of the same opinion, is a monster.”Voltaire</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umartigan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Martigan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1157<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:02:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> Chiteng, same with me and my wife. I am more tense when grouped with my wife than when playing at the same time and doing other things.<br><br>She has her "circle of friends" and so do I. We are actually in two seperate guilds as well. Only once were we both in the same guild (CE in 2000-2001)...but we still didn't hang out much. <p><img src=http://www.garlic.com/~hypatia/images/staff.gif width=460 height=40><br><i>Everybody loves a rose. Will you be thankful for the thorns?</i><br><a href="http://www.kaizenx.com/quickcharinfo.asp?charname=Martigan" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.kaizenx.com/images/nbnwkx1.jpg"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukanewilliam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kanewilliam</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_whitespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 388<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:07:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> I'm married.<br><br>My significant other loathes EQ.<br><br>Has for over 3 years.<br><br>I have to make excuses for playing all the time.<br><br>If I have to say, &quot;It's only 40 cents a day, at least i'm not out spending money on beer, and pizza every night.. think of the money i've saved..&quot;  one more time.. I'll explode.<br><br>Thing is, if I ddin't play, we'd be at home.. watching TV.. doing nothing.  It's my hobby and it's hard to explain how a computer game can be a hobby.<br><br>Ahh well.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=krrak>Krrak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:08:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> A good friend of our's did the smart thing - got us both addicted to EQ at around the same time. At first we did the one computer thing - then finally we got a second one - this was before they allowed character transfers, so she had to start over again - but now we are both in our 50's (with our mains) and have some char's that we only play together and some that we play whenever. We don't always group together but we are always available to port, rez or help the other if need arises.<br><br>I think the only way this game will not destroy marriages is if both spouses have at least tried, if not enjoy the game. It makes understanding the craziness that we do much easier.<br><br>My 2 coppers.... <p>Baron Krrak<br>54 Monk<br>Officer of the <a href="http://www.slackman.com/sunrunners">Sunrunners</a><br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=213902">Magelo Profile</a><br><a href="http://www.spacefem.com/blobs.shtml"><img src="http://spacefemsplanet.com/3dblobs/blobcanuk.gif" width="90" height="98" border="0" alt="Adopt your own useless blob!"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzelgreyweather.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zel Greyweather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:09:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> All/most of the married people I knew in EQ eventually got divorced. =/  I could count a few... so not that many, I guess.<br><br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=318195">ChamCham Silverstar</a> <BR> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=316740">Zelgadis Greyweather</a> <BR> < ChamCham Protectorate ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaishen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aishen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1112<br> 