ase. I dont even know why I got so into it, but I dont plan to ever buy or play another MMoRPG. When PC dies, or when EQ dies, or when I decide to leave that's it. So.. I guess I wouldnt want a fiance really into video games because after EQ I'll be done with it. But for now its a very good thing that Neij plays, too. With all the hours I spend, mostly in the evenings when we are both not at work, if he didnt play also we'd never have time together.  <p><center> <IMG SRC="http://web.tampabay.rr.com/staticpulse/Velondra.jpg"> <br>60th Ranger<br>Proud Dragon Bait of Phoenix Crusaders <br>Beloved of Neijek Domisilva </img> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucassaendra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassaendra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:40:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> Ideal marriage would it be a &quot;spouse that plays as well, but still gives [me] freedom in game to hang out with friends,&quot; which is the way it is with my husband and I. We're not dependent on one another in the enjoyment of the game, but it adds to the game when we can share our experiences. <br><br>(on raids, we're typically not grouped together so strategically it works out because we can tell each other what's going on in our group for healing/taunting)<br><br>...and our lives are more like eq, work, sex, eat, sleep with a movie and shopping thrown in there every once in a while.<br><br>Edit:  Reread and thought that sounded cold...after all, my husband did PL me for a nice chunk of my levels (we were 30+ levels apart, and are now 2 levels apart).  We enjoy grouping quite often. The same-house thing is great because if we don't have anything to do on EQ, we can group/exp together or I can port him around, etc.  Also, we know what the other will do in any given situation. <br><br>Martigan, you were in the same guild (NB) as me *briefly* with Laura, weren't you?   <p><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Tokyo/Ginza/8490">Cassaendra</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87512">56th season wildflower of Tunare</a><br><br><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl"><IMG BORDER=0 ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=80 SRC="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame/0.png" ALT="What Video Game Character Are You? I am Pacman." /></A>I am <B>Pacman</B>.<BR /><BR />I am an aggressive sort of personality, out to get what I can, when I can. I prefer to avoid confrontation, but sometimes when it's called for, I can be a powerful character. I tend to be afflicted with munchies constantly. <A HREF="http://blog.ravenblack.net/quiz/videogame.pl">What Video Game Character Are You?</A> <br><br><b>I am a:</b> Lawful Neutral Ranger Druid  (Find out <a href='http://www.students.uiuc.edu/~ellingwd/dndwho/index.html' target='mt'>What D&D Character Are You?</a>, courtesy of <a href='mailto:ellingwd@uiuc.edu'>NeppyMan</a>!)<br></TD></TR></TABLE><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucassaendra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassaendra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/31/02 11:03:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucezero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cezero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 10:50:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ &amp; Marriage</span><hr size=1> My wife and I play side by side.<br><br>We co-lead our Guild, and it works out well.  I am the more &quot;militaristic&quot; of us, and she is more diplomatic.  This combination has helped keep our guild together, and helped it maintain a largely &quot;friendly&quot; atmosphere, yet still a guild that is growing more and more into a raiding guild.<br><br>In our younger (levelwise) days, we always grouped together, and to this day, we are a package deal for the most part.  However, during raids we actually go out of our way to NOT group together.  This allows better management of our raid forces.<br><br>Also, sometimes one of us will play when the other one doesn't feal like it.  This isn't very common, however, since my wife and I are best friends (and were so before we started dating/got married) so usually if we're not playing EQ, we're doing something else together anyway.<br><br>We also sometimes spend time, in game, doing seperate activities.  This happens often when she's working on trade skills, or we're helping Guildies.  Rarely do we &quot;XP&quot; without each other, but often she'll be in Thurg working on Jewelcraft while I'm porting around doing Guild Invites or other &quot;management&quot; duties.<br><br>-Bumamgar, 53rd Warrior, Co-Leader, Cries of Insurrection <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umartigan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Martigan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1158<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 12:09:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255